  "Made By Mixing Crushed Marble Dust With A Polyester Resin, Cultured Marble Table Tops Are Designed To Mimic The Look Feel Of Natural Marble, But More Affordable, Lighter In Weight, And Easier To Maintain. Cultured Marble Table Tops Are Resistant To Scratches, Stains, And Heat. Additionally, They Are Non-Porous, Which Means They Do Not Absorb Liquids, Making Them Easy To Clean And Maintain For Restaurants, Cafes, Bars, And Hotels.": "_assets/media/16e093345f6070951e46e9a2a8b4e0e9.jpg",
  "Cultured Marble": "_assets/media/e7beafa4845083f6ff30d156b1445f30.jpg",
  "Using Rubberwood Ashes, Compressed Rubberwood Tabletops Are Produced Under Higher Pressure And Temperature. Their Dense, Durable, And Uniform Structure Makes Them More Stable, Water & Stain & Heat Resistance, And Less Prone To Shrinking, Cracking Or Even Splitting From The Edges As Laminate Table Tops. With 14 Colors And Three Types Of Surface Finishings (Smooth, Sandy, Supermatt), It Is A Versatile Choice For All Comercial Settings.": "_assets/media/6576ab95d52f388c869076fd218e9de4.png",
